    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The discovery protocol is time dependent. This was added as a protective measure. Hence if the clocks are not synced to a maximum of ~30 second drift from each other, the nodes will never find each other, so they will not be able to do any data exchanges.\r\n\r\nManually adding one peer to the other (or configuring via a static peer) might get over this limitation. Although I agree that having the concept of time in the protocol is ugly, it's not something easy to get rid of.",
